$OpenBSD$

Add OpenBSD support for process information retrieval using sysctl(3).

On OpenBSD, /proc is not typically mounted and has a different layout
than Linux. Use sysctl(3) with KERN_PROC for process info (UID, command
name), KERN_PROC_ARGS for command line, and KERN_PROC_CWD for working
directory. This enables proper tab title tracking, sudo detection, and
directory tracking in the terminal.

